pytenno.models.locations

class pytenno.models.locations.Location(id: str, icon: str, thumb: str, faction: Faction, name: str, node_name: str)[source]

Represents a location.

Parameters

  • id (str) – The ID of the location.

  • icon (str) – The icon URL of the location.

  • thumb (str) – The thumbnail URL of the location.

  • faction (Faction) – The faction of the location.

  • name (str) – The name of the location.

  • node_name (str) – The name of the node the location is on.
